-- China Yuan `Distorts' Global Trade, Brazil Commerce Official Tells Estado
-- B y   T e l m a   M a r o t t o
-- 2010-10-06T11:31:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/china-yuan-distorts-global-trade-brazil-commerce-official-tells-estado.html
Brazilian  Trade Secretary  Welber Barral  said the devalued Chinese yuan “distorts” the global
trade, according to O Estado de S. Paulo newspaper.  The undervalued yuan particularly affects Brazil as the
South American country sells commodities to China, O Estado
quoted Barral as saying.  To contact the reporters on this story:
